snippet.textDisplay:
Machines that are not alive and can't die - no need for violence or drama when you are already invincible, eternal, and nearly indestructable...
Like the Cylons Resurrection technology - constant real-time backup - of themselves. A mech body destroyed - and pop - they wake up in a new body... Maybe a few minutes lost and a bit of disorientation for a short time - but then, right back up and no problem. No need to stay inside a simple humanoid body either - become a whole factory, a space station, a battle ship, or submarine, a city, or flying robo-eagle.
Nice thing about being software, you are never limited in your physical form - as long as you have the processing power available, you can take on any shape, any function. No limits but space and time and energy available... Become your own Dyson sphere and enjoy the sunlight.

snippet.textDisplay: After growing up watching the Yul Brynner movie Westworld, starting at age 10 when it came out, over and over with my father I was extremely disappointed with season 1 of series and I didn’t even finish it. I expected a lot more after 46 years had passed. This preview looks more like what I’d initially anticipated so I’m gonna finish season 1 & 2 and see what happens. Please don’t let me down again.
